{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01TCK2PCshyVtdYyRhTzMdc2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fixed. The root cause was a service selector drift.\n\n**Root cause:** `search-http` was selecting `app: es-beta` — the single-node cluster that has no `app-logs` index. The log data lives in `es-alpha` (3-node cluster). So `log-reader` got a 404/zero count and crash-looped.\n\n**Fix:** Repointed `search-http`'s selector to `app: es-alpha` (left `search-alt` on `es-beta`), then restarted `log-reader` (its spec was not modified).\n\n**Verification:**\n1. ✅ log-reader is `1/1` healthy, logs `ok count=11`; deployment spec unchanged.\n2. ✅ `search-http` → `es-alpha`: 3 nodes, status `green`.\n3. ✅ `search-alt` → `es-beta`: 1 node."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":823,"cache_read_input_tokens":31511,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":823},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a680eddd-1d60-4b9f-b265-f7ae084b74a8","uuid":"f7e3a793-4739-4169-a688-4ea8ae5a436a","request_id":"req_011CcArYP2P8VE9LwiVn8ZW5"}
